arch sign
name special container drops
msg
Special (one drops) are special in the way,
the item itself is not marked as "one_drop 1".
In that case the item is given when NOT a clone
is in the inventory. The item is also NOT put in
the one_drop quest container.
That means, that this item can drop several times
when dropped!
It makes sense for quest items like keys.
The items should be marked as "quest items"
and as "NO-DROP" to avoid abuse of it.
endmsg
x 5
y 4
end
arch floor_ostone1
x 5
y 5
end
arch floor_ostone1
x 5
y 6
end
arch sign
name one drop container quest
msg
Basic one drop quest.
Item is given the player when the container is opened..
The item is put also as clone in the quest_container
for one drops. As often the player opens the container
again, the quest code knows the item was given
before and it don't drops again - one drop.
endmsg
x 5
y 6
end
arch floor_ostone1
x 5
y 7
end
arch floor_ostone1
x 5
y 8
end
arch sign
name one drop container - with level requirement
msg
Same as the basic one drop, except the player
has to have same or higher level as the
"item_level" of the quest trigger object.
endmsg
x 5
y 8
end
